Reasoning: The paper presents a framework for converting gated camera images into high-resolution depth maps, which involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as semantic context exploitation and synthetic discriminator loss. The resulting system is a replacement for scanning lidar systems, which are commonly used in robotics (RO) and autonomous vehicles. The proposed architecture is trained using machine learning (ML) techniques, specifically deep learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also presents results on real-world data, which suggests that it has practical applications. Overall, the paper is likely to be classified under computer vision (cs.CV), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CVPR).
